<br>
1. i have a lvl 11 high elf mage but i was thinking of making a gnome mage for some reason. i think its because i like to be a little dude with a robe that runs really fast hehe. <br>
2. what woudl u guys recommend me lvling from 30-40?<br>
<br>
3. now i know that every different pet is used for different situations. but alot of people have been using fire pet to solo. i was thinkin since fire pets have low life, they wouldnt be good at soloing. basically i want a pet that i can use to solo, which can kill the mob fast,a nd make it so that i can keep on chain pulling before i have to med and stuff.<br>
<br>
4.i heard about pet canni'ing and i was wondering, shoudl i use it? and if so what lvl should i start? and when i hit 44 shoudl i use that? or romt? tnx in advance <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krilenspiritlink>Krilen Spiritlink</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 591<br> <font color=#333333>(12/14/02 5:21:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8156.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: hey guys, new mage, please read</span><hr size=1> 1) Hopefully this thread will not erupt into the so overdone race discussion. It's really up to you. There's no huge difference between high elf and gnome. If you feel you can get those 11 levels again and that the time to get back those 11 levels is worth being the race you're more interested in, go for it. Your call.<br>
<br>
2) I don't understand the question. If you're asking what to kill, I'll give you the same answer I give everyone who asks what to kill at any level: Find blue mobs and kill them. Exp differs like 0.1% from zone to zone(non-planar zones anyway), so you'll only take like 2 kills off a level by fighting in a good exp-mod zone. Find blue mobs. Kill them.<br>
<br>
3) You won't get a straight answer on this either. There's no best choice, because it depends on what the rest of your strat is. If you're gonna heal your pet, hell yeah use fire. If you nuke a lot but can't kite or tank, earth might be neccessary to take the agro off you with root. Air and Water's abilities are too vague to describe a specific situation where they would be far and away the best. My advice for this one, is when you go to fight new mobs, test out all the pets and go with whichever works best against those mobs.<br>
<br>
4) Don't worry about pet canni until you get spell casting mastery AA, or at least level 49, a horse, summoning efficiency item, and regeant preservation item(can summon one)<br>
<br>
